{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Shopify Theme from Scratch Part 8: article.liquid","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>\t\t\t\t<div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:23.25%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/19bd1/part8_banner.png 163w,\n/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/d3bcb/part8_banner.png 325w,\n/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/dbb61/part8_banner.png 650w,\n/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/8ff1e/part8_banner.png 800w\" src=\"/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/dbb61/part8_banner.png\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/19bd1/part8_banner.png 163w,\n/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/d3bcb/part8_banner.png 325w,\n/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/dbb61/part8_banner.png 650w,\n/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/8ff1e/part8_banner.png 800w\" src=\"/static/71f2da5cf99b96bc02b021545665e2c0/dbb61/part8_banner.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></p>\n<p>Once a user clicks on an article listed on the blog.liquid template, they are taken to the article.liquid template. The article.liquid template is where the full article is shown. Users also have the option to leave comments to articles through this template.</p>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s butter some biscuits!</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">1. Output the article content and information</h2>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s start off by outputting the article&#x2019;s content and information (publish date, number of comments, tags). I won&#x2019;t go into too much detail here as it&#x2019;s essentially the same code from Part 7 :). A for-loop is not necessary here because we&#x2019;re only outputting one article, i.e. the one that we&#x2019;re currently viewing. We&#x2019;re also replacing {{ article.excerpt_or_content }} with just {{ article.content }}, because there is no need to output the excerpt here.</p>\n<p>Open the article.liquid template, and replace its contents with the following code:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<div class=\"blog-article single-article\">\n  <h1 class=\"blog-title\">{{ article.title }}</h1>\n  <div class=\"blog-data\">\n    {{ article.published_at | date: &apos;%b %d, %Y&apos; }}\n    {% if blog.comments_enabled? %}\n    - <a href=\"{{ article.url }}#comments\">{{ article.comments_count }} {{ article.comments_count | pluralize: &apos;comment&apos;,&apos;comments&apos; }}</a>\n    {% endif %}\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"blog-content rte\">\n    {{ article.content }}\n  </div>\n  {% if article.tags.size &gt; 0 %}\n  <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n    tags:\n    {% for tag in article.tags %} \n    <a href=\"{{ blog.url }}/tagged/{{ tag | handle }}\">{{ tag }}</a>{% unless forloop.last %}, {% endunless %}\n    {% endfor %}\n  </div>  \n  {% endif %}\n</div>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>You should now see the contents of the article being output, as well as the date, the number of comments, and tags (if the article contains tags), as shown in Figure 8.1.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/article-template.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:60.58823529411765%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/aca85/article-template.jpg 163w,\n/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/0954f/article-template.jpg 325w,\n/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/a111b/article-template.jpg 650w,\n/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/ce471/article-template.jpg 975w,\n/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/5d177/article-template.jpg 1020w\" src=\"/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/a111b/article-template.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/aca85/article-template.jpg 163w,\n/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/0954f/article-template.jpg 325w,\n/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/a111b/article-template.jpg 650w,\n/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/ce471/article-template.jpg 975w,\n/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/5d177/article-template.jpg 1020w\" src=\"/static/c0367847a3ef3fb45275afa9aa561026/a111b/article-template.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 8.1: Contents of a single article being output.</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">2. List the article comments</h2>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s start off by writing some Liquid to check if the storeowner has comments enabled.  After all, there&#x2019;s no point in outputting comments or a comment form if the storeowner has blog comments disabled! Blog comments are enabled in the Blog details page in the admin (Figure 8.2)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/blog-comment-settings.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:58.20063694267515%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/aca85/blog-comment-settings.jpg 163w,\n/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/0954f/blog-comment-settings.jpg 325w,\n/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/a111b/blog-comment-settings.jpg 650w,\n/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/ce471/blog-comment-settings.jpg 975w,\n/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/98c72/blog-comment-settings.jpg 1256w\" src=\"/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/a111b/blog-comment-settings.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/aca85/blog-comment-settings.jpg 163w,\n/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/0954f/blog-comment-settings.jpg 325w,\n/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/a111b/blog-comment-settings.jpg 650w,\n/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/ce471/blog-comment-settings.jpg 975w,\n/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/98c72/blog-comment-settings.jpg 1256w\" src=\"/static/3873f89d98cafe3e542a75a4f54522ea/a111b/blog-comment-settings.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 8.2: Blog details page of the admin</div>\n<p>At the bottom of the article.liquid, add the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n...\n  <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n    tags:\n    {% for tag in article.tags %} \n    <a href=\"{{ blog.url }}/tagged/{{ tag | handle }}\">{{ tag }}</a>{% unless forloop.last %}, {% endunless %}\n    {% endfor %}\n  </div>  \n  {% endif %}\n\n\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% if blog.comments_enabled? %}\n\n{% endif %}</span>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>This if-statement checks to see if comments are enabled in the blog&#x2019;s settings.</p>\n<p>Now let&#x2019;s go ahead and output the comments that have been added to the blog. Between the if-statement that we just added, insert the following code in red:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n{% if blog.comments_enabled? %}\n\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% if article.comments.size &gt; 0 %}\n<div class=\"comments\">\n  <h2>Comments ({{ article.comments_count }})</h2>\n  {% for comment in article.comments %}\n  <div class=\"comment\">\n    <div class=\"comment-data\">\n      <span class=\"comment-author\">{{ comment.author }}</span> <small>on {{ comment.created_at | date: &quot;%B %d, %Y&quot; }}</small>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"comment-content\">\n      {{ comment.content }}\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  {% endfor %}\n</div>\n{% endif %}</span>\n\n{% endif %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Here, we&#x2019;re looping through the &#x2018;comments&#x2019; array of the current article, and accessing the variables of each &#x2018;comment&#x2019; object. This includes information such as the author of the comment, the email of the author of the comment, when it was written, etc. To see a full list of the comment object&#x2019;s variables, please see this <a href=\"http://docs.shopify.com/themes/liquid-variables/article#comment-attributes\">page</a>.</p>\n<p>If you&#x2019;re working on a fresh shop, you may not have any article comments to display yet. If this is the case you can add some through the form that we&#x2019;re going to be creating in the next step.</p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">3. Add the comment form</h2>\n<p>Directly below the if-statement that checks for &#x201C;article.comments.size &gt; 0&#x201D;, paste the code in red below.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n...\n\n{% if article.comments.size &gt; 0 %}\n<div class=\"comments\">\n  <h2>Comments ({{ article.comments_count }})</h2>\n  {% for comment in article.comments %}\n  <div class=\"comment\">\n    <div class=\"comment-data\">\n      <strong>{{ comment.author }}</strong> <small>on {{ comment.created_at | date: &quot;%B %d, %Y&quot; }}</small>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"comment-content\">\n      {{ comment.content }}\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  {% endfor %}\n</div>\n{% endif %}\n\n<span style=\"color:red;\"><div class=\"comment-form\">\n  {% form article %}\n  <h2>Leave a comment:</h2>\n\n  <div class=\"comment-entries\">\n    \n      <label for=\"comment-author\">Name</label>\n      <input {% if form.errors contains \"author\" %} class=\"error\" endif type=\"text\" name=\"comment[author]\" placeholder=\"Your name\" value=\"{{ form.author }}\">\n    \n\n    \n      <label for=\"comment-email\">Email</label>\n      <input {% if form.errors contains \"email\" %} class=\"error\" endif type=\"email\" name=\"comment[email]\" placeholder=\"your@email.com\" value=\"{{ form.email }}\">\n    \n\n    \n      <label for=\"comment-body\">Message</label>\n      <textarea {% if form.errors contains \"body\" %} class=\"error\" endif name=\"comment[body]\">{{ form.body }}</textarea>\n    \n\n  </div>\n  <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Post Comment!\" class=\"btn\"> \n\n  {% endform %}\n</div></span>\n{% endif %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>This will give you a snazzy comment form that will allow visitors to leave comments to articles (Figure 8.3).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/article-comment-form.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:78.29534192269574%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/aca85/article-comment-form.jpg 163w,\n/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/0954f/article-comment-form.jpg 325w,\n/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/a111b/article-comment-form.jpg 650w,\n/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/ce471/article-comment-form.jpg 975w,\n/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/0110e/article-comment-form.jpg 1009w\" src=\"/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/a111b/article-comment-form.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/aca85/article-comment-form.jpg 163w,\n/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/0954f/article-comment-form.jpg 325w,\n/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/a111b/article-comment-form.jpg 650w,\n/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/ce471/article-comment-form.jpg 975w,\n/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/0110e/article-comment-form.jpg 1009w\" src=\"/static/48eb9bc4f2bc6ed767f56cf6f0065468/a111b/article-comment-form.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 8.3: The blog comments form </div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">4. Adding error/success messages</h2>\n<p>Next, we need to add some error checking to prevent visitors from submitting incomplete forms. This is made easy thanks to the form objects&#x2019; &#x201C;errors&#x201D; variable.</p>\n<p>Still inside article.liquid, insert the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n...\n</code><div class=\"comment-form\"><code markup=\"span\">\n  {% form article %}\n  <h2>Leave a comment:</h2>\n\n  <span style=\"color:red;\">{% if form.errors %}\n  <div class=\"errors\">\n    {{ settings.comments_error_message }}\n    {% for field in form.errors %}\n    The {{ field | capitalize | replace: &apos;Body&apos;, &apos;Message&apos; }} field {{ form.errors.messages[field] }}.\n    {% endfor %}\n  </div>\n  {% endif %}\n  {% if form.posted_successfully? %}\n  <div class=\"success\">\n    \n    {% if blog.moderated? %}\n      Your comment needs to be approved by the blog owner.\n    {% else %}\n      Successfully posted your comment.\n    {% endif %}\n    \n  </div>\n  {% endif %}</span>\n\n  </code><div class=\"comment-entries\"><code markup=\"span\">\n    \n      <label for=\"comment-author\">Name</label>\n      <input {% if form.errors contains \"author\" %} class=\"error\" endif type=\"text\" name=\"comment[author]\" placeholder=\"Your name\" value=\"{{ form.author }}\">\n    \n...\n</code>\n\n<p>Now, when you try to submit a comment without properly filling out the form, you will be shown an error message (Figure 8.4).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">\n<a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/form-error.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:99.16201117318435%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 358px) 100vw, 358px\" srcset=\"/static/826afada588a270d1077c0e74b04cb6c/aca85/form-error.jpg 163w,\n/static/826afada588a270d1077c0e74b04cb6c/0954f/form-error.jpg 325w,\n/static/826afada588a270d1077c0e74b04cb6c/ead38/form-error.jpg 358w\" src=\"/static/826afada588a270d1077c0e74b04cb6c/ead38/form-error.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 358px) 100vw, 358px\" srcset=\"/static/826afada588a270d1077c0e74b04cb6c/aca85/form-error.jpg 163w,\n/static/826afada588a270d1077c0e74b04cb6c/0954f/form-error.jpg 325w,\n/static/826afada588a270d1077c0e74b04cb6c/ead38/form-error.jpg 358w\" src=\"/static/826afada588a270d1077c0e74b04cb6c/ead38/form-error.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a>\n</p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 8.4: An error message is returned if a customer does not complete the comment form</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">5. Add the CSS</h2>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s go ahead and pretty up the article page. Open style.css, and insert the CSS code below at the very bottom of the CSS file.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n/**** article.liquid ****/ \n\n.single-article{border-bottom:none; margin-bottom: 0;}\n\n.comments{border-top:1px solid #ccc; margin-bottom:30px;}\n.comment{margin-bottom: 30px;}\n.comment-author{font-weight:bold; font-size:20px;}\n\n.comment-entries label, .comment-entries input, .comment-entries textarea{ display:block;}\n.comment-entries label{font-size:14px;}\n.comment-entries input, .comment-entries textarea{border: 1px solid #ccc; padding:5px;}\n.comment-entries textarea{width:350px; height:180px;}\n\n.errors{color:#e00000;}\n.error{border: 1px solid #e00000 !important;}\n.success{color:#5BB85E;}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Your article page should now look like this:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/article-final-1.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:85.92814371257485%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/aca85/article-final-1.jpg 163w,\n/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/0954f/article-final-1.jpg 325w,\n/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/a111b/article-final-1.jpg 650w,\n/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/ce471/article-final-1.jpg 975w,\n/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/4450c/article-final-1.jpg 1002w\" src=\"/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/a111b/article-final-1.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/aca85/article-final-1.jpg 163w,\n/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/0954f/article-final-1.jpg 325w,\n/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/a111b/article-final-1.jpg 650w,\n/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/ce471/article-final-1.jpg 975w,\n/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/4450c/article-final-1.jpg 1002w\" src=\"/static/1ff84bee787b3b2b55f3fede00b55376/a111b/article-final-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<p>The CSS includes styles for the form and its error/success messages as well &#x1F642;</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/errors-styled.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:141.20603015075375%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 398px) 100vw, 398px\" srcset=\"/static/58963e193cde650decd7c7e2ef423e09/aca85/errors-styled.jpg 163w,\n/static/58963e193cde650decd7c7e2ef423e09/0954f/errors-styled.jpg 325w,\n/static/58963e193cde650decd7c7e2ef423e09/6d9d2/errors-styled.jpg 398w\" src=\"/static/58963e193cde650decd7c7e2ef423e09/6d9d2/errors-styled.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 398px) 100vw, 398px\" srcset=\"/static/58963e193cde650decd7c7e2ef423e09/aca85/errors-styled.jpg 163w,\n/static/58963e193cde650decd7c7e2ef423e09/0954f/errors-styled.jpg 325w,\n/static/58963e193cde650decd7c7e2ef423e09/6d9d2/errors-styled.jpg 398w\" src=\"/static/58963e193cde650decd7c7e2ef423e09/6d9d2/errors-styled.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<p>That&#x2019;s it for this week!</p>\n<p><a href=\"/shopify-theme-from-scratch/\">&#x2190; Back to table of contents</a>\t\t</p>\n</div></div></pre></body></html>","wordpress_id":3404},"allWordpressWpComments":{"edges":[{"node":{"content":"<p>YEAH!!!!  nice TUTS TETCHI!!!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://prntscr.com/btzvgq\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://prntscr.com/btzvgq</a></p>\n","author_name":"Raniel","date":"July 17th, 2016"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Hey Are, sorry man I&#8217;m not sure if I understand your question.</p>\n","author_name":"tetchi","date":"August 3rd, 2013"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Hi, I&#8217;m working now on article.liquid, i&#8217;m  trying to change the way how the images and the text of the article are shown, Like a grid of the images and all the text of the article aligned to de right. I just can&#8217;t access to the images, for putting a css on . Or this just can be made at the moment when you are making the post? Thanks!</p>\n","author_name":"Are","date":"July 31st, 2013"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>A Windows Editor would be nice, for sure. </p>\n<p>All core functionalities will be in the theme, i.e. customers will be able to browse through products, add products to the cart, make customer accounts, etc. through this basic theme.</p>\n","author_name":"tetchi","date":"June 4th, 2013"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Woohoo! Finally caught up with you :). You really need to tell the devs to make a Desktop Editor for Windows&#8230;broke my mac and waiting for the new one to come out and I can only do the next best thing here, which is write all this up in Sublime and then copy and paste the entire file every time into Shopify.</p>\n<p>One question &#8211; if someone builds an entire theme from scratch through this tutorial (and up to this part), how comprehensive is it, exactly? What I mean by that is will all core functionality be covered to the extent that no links/options should break anywhere on a site?</p>\n","author_name":"Ben","date":"June 4th, 2013"}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-8","wordpressId":3404,"newerPostSlug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-9","olderPostSlug":"shopify-theme-settings-assigning-colors-dynamically-using-sass"}}